A yet-to-be identified man has lost his life after a stray bullet allegedly fired by Special Anti-Robbery Squad officers hit him at Ajisegiri street in the Palmgroove area of Lagos state this morning, Monday July 15th. Information by an eyewitness revealed that the man who sweeps the street, was busy with his job when the SARS officers engaged some Cannibis smokers in a hot chase and fired gunshots at the Cannibis smokers. Sadly, the bullet hit the deceased who died instantly. The SARS officers fled the scene immediately the incident happened. Source